<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="339" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new specific epithet is derived from the Latin adjective “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cao &amp; Dmitriev" authorityYear="2020" box="[1050,1117,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Etmaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="339" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[1050,1117,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” which means short, small, referring to the short preatrial processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="339" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,294,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dworakowska)" authorityName="Cao &amp; Dmitriev &amp; Dietrich &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dworakowska" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[659,995,295,322]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Etmaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="339" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decembris">
<emphasis box="[659,805,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="339">E. decembris</emphasis>
(Dworakowska)
</taxonomicName>
, but the anal tube appendage is broader and curved, the pygofer ventral appendage is curved, the style has a much longer apex, and the aedeagal shaft is curved dorso-cephalad with the dorso-lateral edges serrated and lamelliform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
